{"nodes": [{"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_checkout_pattern", "label": "Take money / checkout pattern (customer mapping before session, webhook entitles)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Persisting the customer mapping before creating a checkout session lets the webhook treat an unresolvable customer as not-ours and ignore it. Nothing on the success redirect path grants access; only the webhook entitles. Routes answer with a URL, not a 3xx, since the caller is a client-side fetch."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_provider_webhook_pattern", "label": "Receive a provider webhook pattern (signature auth, raw body, marker+effect in one tx, watermark)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Signature is the authentication so the route must be exempted from the session guard; request.text() reads the raw body since re-serializing invalidates the signature; idempotency marker+effect commit in one transaction; a provider event timestamp watermark guards against out-of-order retries."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_super_admin_action_pattern", "label": "Super-admin action pattern (requireSuperAdmin() first line, no super-admin middleware)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "proxy.ts is edge-safe with no DB access, so the only edge-available alternative (a cookie claim) is invalidated by impersonation swapping the session cookie; audit Rule A/Rule B split by who owns the DB connection; never read the session after a cookie swap."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_org_scoped_rbac_action_pattern", "label": "Org-scoped RBAC action pattern (requireOrgPermission(slug, permission) first line)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Resolves the active org from the URL slug, checks the centralized role-permission map, and calls Next's forbidden() for a real 403; UI gating via hasPermission is cosmetic only; the active tenant is always derived from the /orgs/[slug] URL, never hidden session state."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_csp_third_party_origin_pattern", "label": "CSP third-party origin pattern (env-driven extra src, strict-dynamic, nonce)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "CSP is default-deny; script-src uses strict-dynamic so host allowlists are ignored by supporting browsers; the CSP header is set only in the proxy (per-request nonce) never duplicated in next.config.ts, since repeated CSP headers intersect."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_rate_limit_tuning_pattern", "label": "Rate limit tuning pattern (tierFor first-match-wins, report-only mode, forwarded depth)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "RATE_LIMIT_FORWARDED_DEPTH is security-critical - set wrong, the limiter is bypassable by rotating a header; billing webhook and cron endpoints are exempt because throttling them would be actively harmful; login limit is enforced separately by the server action itself since it never matches an /api rule."}, {"id": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_feature_flag_pattern", "label": "Cosmetic feature flag pattern (MULTI_TENANCY_MODE, orgsEnabled/orgsExposed, notFound not forbidden)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two booleans (orgsEnabled/orgsExposed) instead of a three-way switch per call site; the data model never moves in any mode; a switched-off feature refuses with notFound(), never forbidden(), since a 403 admits the resource exists; enforcement lives at the existing requireOrgAccess chokepoint, not the proxy."}], "edges": [{"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_checkout_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_05_checkout", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_checkout_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_05_customer_portal", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_checkout_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_05_plany_i_ceny", "relation": "conceptually_related_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_checkout_pattern", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_jobs_adapter_transactional_outbox", "relation": "shares_data_with", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_provider_webhook_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_05_webhooki", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_provider_webhook_pattern", "target": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_a_jobs_adapter_transactional_outbox", "relation": "semantically_similar_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.85, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_provider_webhook_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_12_wymagania_jobs", "relation": "semantically_similar_to", "confidence": "INFERRED", "confidence_score": 0.75, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_super_admin_action_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_06_dostep_super_admin", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "docs_architecture_reference_patterns_c_super_admin_action_pattern", "target": "docs_boilerplate_spec_06_audit_log", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/architecture/reference-patterns/c-platnosci-bezpieczenstwo-flagi.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source